Go to EC2:
Create a new instance - 
  choose ubuntu, t2.micro
  Create a new key pair 
    - name as ”notes-key” then choose RSA and format is .pem
    - Add security group rule : Custom TCP and port = 8000, anywhere

Connect to instance (terminal)
Click instance → click: Connect
Choose tab: EC2 Instance Connect
Click: Connect
Run this command:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm -y
git clone https://github.com/AnkitaRaj2003/cloud-lab.git
cd cloud-lab/full-stack-app/backend
npm install
node server.js

To remove: rm -rf cloud-lab

